<span id="freeTextContainer8364823662416109090">I really liked this sweet kid&apos;s voice. The author does it perfectly--his own voice never intrudes. I liked the way racism is touched on several times, because it&apos;s an inescapable part of Bud&apos;s life, but not dwelt on, because that isn&apos;t what the story&apos;s about.<br/><br/>It has something of a fantasy ending, but that&apos;s maybe not such a bad thing here.</span>
  <span id="freeText8364823662416109090" style="display:none">I really liked this sweet kid's voice. The author does it perfectly--his own voice never intrudes. I liked the way racism is touched on several times, because it's an inescapable part of Bud's life, but not dwelt on, because that isn't what the story's about.<br /><br />It has something of a fantasy ending, but that's maybe not such a bad thing here.</span>
