  <span id="freeText17691553112733736968" style="display:none">Young, opportunistic Bud learns that when one door closes another one opens as he ventures on his quest to find his family and keep his mother's memory alive. <br /><br />I listened to the audiobook of this story, read by the one and only James Avery (you may know him as Uncle Phil from Fresh Prince of Bel Air). Another bonus of the audiobook (besides the jazzy music) is that author Christopher Paul Curtis provides background on his family (the inspiration for the book), and one of the songs featured in the narrative gets to be heard by viewers.</span>
